    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Water Pump and Thermostat -
        Install - Coolant Filter
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210011004.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Coolant Filter</title>
        <para>Coolant filter can only be installed if engine is off stand.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new O-ring and seal in rear of coolant filter header.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install coolant filter header on mounting pad of front cover and fasten with mounting bolts.
                Tighten bolts to "
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_267.xml" xrefid="t210011002">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                ."
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate coolant filter gasket with clean engine oil and install new coolant filter.
                Tighten coolant filter until gasket contacts coolant filter header. Tighten filter one additional full
                turn.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Open manual shutoff valve by turning it counterclockwise. When open, handle will be pointing
                rearward.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210011014" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8044.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install coolant filter</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Lever</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant filter</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
